Data Scientist – Prediction and Statistical Machine Learning Specialist		Njf Global Holdings Ltd		Berkeley, CA, US		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><strong>Listing Info<br /><br /></strong>This position will involve working within a hedge fund that applies a scientific-driven systematic approach to trading stocks, futures and foreign exchange. The firm specializes in the application of statistical machine learning to large, high-dimensional data sets and extracts the patterns, correlations and periodicities which can be traded by systematic strategies. The role will involve preparing data for analysis, model development and model implementation. The role will involve working with a former statistics professor as well as PhD's from Berkeley, Stanford, CMU, and other top-tier schools.<br /><br /><strong>Requirements<br /><br /><br /></strong><ul> <li>A PhD is required - with a focus on statistical machine learning</li> <li>GPA of 3.9 or higher</li> <li>Background in modern statistical methods and machine learning </li> <li>Evidence of strong mathematical abilities, e.g. publication record, or competition placement </li> <li>Substantial programming experience and interest in software development techniques </li> <li>Competence in solving large-scale computing problems </li> <li>Track record as an applied researcher </li> <li>Demonstrable clarity of thought (not optional) Interest in financial applications is essential, but experience in finance is not a primary factor in our hiring.</li> <br /><br /></ul><strong>Benefits<br /></strong><ul><li>Benefits and compensation are highly competitive.</li></ul></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">NJF Global Holdings is a privately owned portfolio of recruitment and executive search companies. The constituent companies cover a multitude of industry sectors and offer services across a diverse spectrum of geographical locations. <br /><br />Our objective is to continue to diversify our Portfolio by bringing our services to new sectors, where we see both long-term sustainability and enough market liquidity, to contribute a significant increase in revenue to our overall portfolio, over the medium and long term. <br /><br />The Group’s headquarters are based in the UK, with offices in New York, Chicago and Nottingham.</div>